                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="perg">
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <material>Parchment.</material>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>5. <dimensions type="leaf" scope="all">
                                        <height unit="mm">223</height>
                                        <width unit="mm">145</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>
                                    <p>The manuscript is provided with a foliation in the upper
                                        right-hand corner. Fol. 4 is foliated 129 by <name
                                            type="person" key="JonSig004">Jón Sigurðsson</name>,
                                        presumably because this leaf once was joined together with
                                            <ref type="ms" target="#AM02-0068-en">AM 68 fol</ref>,
                                        which consists of 128 leaves.</p>
                                </foliation>
                                <condition>
                                    <p>All the leaves, but especially f. 4, are worn and full of
                                        holes and only the inner half of f. 5 is preserved. It is
                                        evident that the leaves once served as binding; one of the
                                        sides of the leaves (1v, 2r, 3v, 4r, 5r) are more worn
                                        because it was the page turning out. In some parts the
                                        parchment has become so dark or the writing so indistinct,
                                        that reading is difficult or impossible.</p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="32">
                                    <p>The manuscript is written in long lines with 32 lines per
                                        page. Rubrics in red, majuscules in red and green.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc hands="1">
                            <handNote script="textualis"><p>The manuscript is written in a clear and
                                    practiced Icelandic Gothic bookhand.</p></handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>A couple of hardly legible marginalia occur on f. 4r.</p>
                        </additions>
                        <accMat>
                            <p>The note on the former front cover written by <name type="person"
                                    key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> is maintained. It writes:
                                    <q xml:lang="is">Fragment ur Olafs Sỏgu Helga egregio Codice.
                                    feinged fra Halfdane Jons syne ä Reykim i ỏlvese.</q>
                            </p>
                        </accMat>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1325" notAfter="1350" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>The manuscript is written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>. <name
                                    type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name> has dated
                                the manuscript to <date>s. XIV</date>, whereas <name type="person"
                                    key="OscJoh001">Oscar Albert Johnsen</name> and <name
                                    type="person" key="JonHel003">Jón Helgason</name> has dated the
                                manuscript more precisely to <origDate notBefore="1325"
                                    notAfter="1350" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">s. XIV <hi
                                        rend="sup">2/4</hi></origDate>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The only known owner of the manuscript is <name type="person"
                                    key="HalJon001">Hálfdan Jónsson</name>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>According to Árni Magnússons note on the old cover (see above) he
                                acquired the manuscript from Hálfdan Jónsson.</p>
                        </acquisition>
